title: For Sale:  Colt Woodsman 1st Model Match Target "Bullseye" Model
postcontent: Colt Woodsman 1st Model Match Target, also called the Bullseye model or Elephant Ear model (due to the long grips). This pistol is original, in very nice condition & looks far better than my photographs. I would say very easily a 95% gun with a little wear on the sharp edges (especially around the muzzle, face of muzzle doesn't have much finish) & on the front of the grip strap. Grips are obviously vintage aftermarket & have a large chip out of the front left side (see photos). The magazine is an original Colt Woodsman magazine. It is 2 line on the bottom, not 3 line, & is not "two tone". It may or may not be original to the pistol, but it is an original Colt & it functions perfectly. A lot of collectors claim that this pistol came with a case hardened two tone magazine & that it had a 3 line "address" on the bottom. I have a Sutherland Colt book & it suggests that it could have come either way. There are 3 initials, CLB, engraved on the left side of the frame which are well done & I feel do not detract from the pistol. I have a factory letter that shows this pistol being shipped to a sporting goods in San Francisco, California in 1941 in a shipment of 10 similar pistols. Pistol is very nice & shoots extremely well. Thank you!
